messages.message:
Aaron, Ted and I chatted, we’re going to introduce a “version” kwarg into our Refiner functions; with this “version”, we’ll now be able to upgrade functions while still maintaining backwards compatibility

this “version” will be by default “1.0" for all existing Refiner programs. For new refiner programs, the “version” will be set to latest, which will be “2.0" soon.

The user may click on Program Settings to change the .ibprog level “version”, or they may change the “version” kwarg in their individual functions if they desire
